  1. #! /usr/bin/perl
  2. #
  3. # Copyright (c) 2001-2024, PostgreSQL Global Development Group
  4. #
  5. # src/backend/utils/mb/Unicode/UCS_to_EUC_JP.pl
  6. #
  7. # Generate UTF-8 <--> EUC_JP code conversion tables from
  8. # map files provided by Unicode organization.
  9. # Unfortunately it is prohibited by the organization
  10. # to distribute the map files. So if you try to use this script,
  11. # you have to obtain CP932.TXT and JIS0212.TXT from the
  12. # organization's ftp site.

  14. use strict;
  15. use warnings FATAL => 'all';

  17. use convutils;

  19. my $this_script = 'src/backend/utils/mb/Unicode/UCS_to_EUC_JP.pl';

  21. # Load JIS0212.TXT
  22. my $jis0212 = &read_source("JIS0212.TXT");

  24. my @mapping;

  26. foreach my $i (@$jis0212)
  27. {

  29.     # We have a different mapping for this in the EUC_JP to UTF-8 direction.
  30.     if ($i->{code} == 0x2243)
  31.     {
  32.         $i->{direction} = FROM_UNICODE;
  33.     }

  35.     if ($i->{code} == 0x2271)
  36.     {
  37.         $i->{direction} = TO_UNICODE;
  38.     }

  40.     if ($i->{ucs} >= 0x080)
  41.     {
  42.         $i->{code} = $i->{code} | 0x8f8080;
  43.     }
  44.     else
  45.     {
  46.         next;
  47.     }

  49.     push @mapping, $i;
  50. }

  52. # Load CP932.TXT.
  53. my $ct932 = &read_source("CP932.TXT");

  55. foreach my $i (@$ct932)
  56. {
  57.     my $sjis = $i->{code};

  59.     # We have a different mapping for this in the EUC_JP to UTF-8 direction.
  60.     if (   $sjis == 0xeefa
  61.         || $sjis == 0xeefb
  62.         || $sjis == 0xeefc)
  63.     {
  64.         next;
  65.     }

  67.     if ($sjis >= 0xa1)
  68.     {
  69.         my $jis = &sjis2jis($sjis);

  71.         $i->{code} = $jis | (
  72.             $jis < 0x100
  73.             ? 0x8e00
  74.             : ($sjis >= 0xeffd ? 0x8f8080 : 0x8080));

  76.         # Remember the SJIS code for later.
  77.         $i->{sjis} = $sjis;

  79.         push @mapping, $i;
  80.     }
  81. }

  83. # extract only SJIS characters
  84. foreach my $i (grep defined $_->{sjis}, @mapping)
  85. {
  86.     my $sjis = $i->{sjis};

  88.     # These SJIS characters are excluded completely.
  89.     if (   $sjis >= 0xed00 && $sjis <= 0xeef9
  90.         || $sjis >= 0xfa54 && $sjis <= 0xfa56
  91.         || $sjis >= 0xfa58 && $sjis <= 0xfc4b)
  92.     {
  93.         $i->{direction} = NONE;
  94.         next;
  95.     }

  97.     # These SJIS characters are only in the UTF-8 to EUC_JP table
  98.     if ($sjis == 0xeefa || $sjis == 0xeefb || $sjis == 0xeefc)
  99.     {
  100.         $i->{direction} = FROM_UNICODE;
  101.         next;
  102.     }

  104.     if (   $sjis == 0x8790
  105.         || $sjis == 0x8791
  106.         || $sjis == 0x8792
  107.         || $sjis == 0x8795
  108.         || $sjis == 0x8796
  109.         || $sjis == 0x8797
  110.         || $sjis == 0x879a
  111.         || $sjis == 0x879b
  112.         || $sjis == 0x879c
  113.         || ($sjis >= 0xfa4a && $sjis <= 0xfa53))
  114.     {
  115.         $i->{direction} = TO_UNICODE;
  116.         next;
  117.     }
  118. }

  120. push @mapping, (
  121.     {
  122.         direction => BOTH,
  123.         ucs => 0x4efc,
  124.         code => 0x8ff4af,
  125.         comment => '# CJK(4EFC)'
  126.     },
  127.     {
  128.         direction => BOTH,
  129.         ucs => 0x50f4,
  130.         code => 0x8ff4b0,
  131.         comment => '# CJK(50F4)'
  132.     },
  133.     {
  134.         direction => BOTH,
  135.         ucs => 0x51EC,
  136.         code => 0x8ff4b1,
  137.         comment => '# CJK(51EC)'
  138.     },
  139.     {
  140.         direction => BOTH,
  141.         ucs => 0x5307,
  142.         code => 0x8ff4b2,
  143.         comment => '# CJK(5307)'
  144.     },
  145.     {
  146.         direction => BOTH,
  147.         ucs => 0x5324,
  148.         code => 0x8ff4b3,
  149.         comment => '# CJK(5324)'
  150.     },
  151.     {
  152.         direction => BOTH,
  153.         ucs => 0x548A,
  154.         code => 0x8ff4b5,
  155.         comment => '# CJK(548A)'
  156.     },
  157.     {
  158.         direction => BOTH,
  159.         ucs => 0x5759,
  160.         code => 0x8ff4b6,
  161.         comment => '# CJK(5759)'
  162.     },
  163.     {
  164.         direction => BOTH,
  165.         ucs => 0x589E,
  166.         code => 0x8ff4b9,
  167.         comment => '# CJK(589E)'
  168.     },
  169.     {

  171.         ucs => 0x5BEC,

  643. #######################################################################
  644. # sjis2jis ; SJIS => JIS conversion
  645. ‌sub sjis2jis
  646. {
  647.     my ($sjis) = @_;

  649.     return $sjis if ($sjis <= 0x100);

  651.     my $hi = $sjis >> 8;
  652.     my $lo = $sjis & 0xff;

  654.     if ($lo >= 0x80) { $lo--; }
  655.     $lo -= 0x40;
  656.     if ($hi >= 0xe0) { $hi -= 0x40; }
  657.     $hi -= 0x81;
  658.     my $pos = $lo + $hi * 0xbc;

  660.     if ($pos >= 114 * 0x5e && $pos <= 115 * 0x5e + 0x1b)
  661.     {

  663.         # This region (115-ku) is out of range of JIS code but for
  664.         # convenient to generate code in EUC CODESET 3, move this to
  665.         # seemingly duplicate region (83-84-ku).
  666.         $pos = $pos - ((31 * 0x5e) + 12);

  668.         # after 85-ku 82-ten needs to be moved 2 codepoints
  669.         $pos = $pos - 2 if ($pos >= 84 * 0x5c + 82);
  670.     }

  672.     my $hi2 = $pos / 0x5e;
  673.     my $lo2 = ($pos % 0x5e);

  675.     my $ret = $lo2 + 0x21 + (($hi2 + 0x21) << 8);

  677.     return $ret;
  678. }
